  "subject": "Modified to use hibernate and jboss JTA",
  "commit_message": "Modified to use hibernate and jboss JTA\n\nModified to use hibernate, exclusively, instead of mixing with eclipselink.\nAlso modified to use jboss JTA instead of bitronix.\nAlso switched to powermock 1.7.1, enabling the removal of the Factory\ninner class from the persistence feature.\nAdded more test cases to EntityMgrTrans to provide coverage for various\nexception types.\nWrapped another RuntimeException in a specific type.\n\nApplied changes to address most of the comments from 11/29:\nMoved object store to features/session-persistence/jta.\nWrapped RuntimeException in specific type.\nModified test to throw specific exception type.\nConverted GenSchema from an @Test to a main().\nLogged caught exceptions in junit tests.\n\nIssue-ID: POLICY-191\nChange-Id: I2f58a49fcd1742d59af8c41e404055bec225a560\nSigned-off-by: Jim Hahn <jrh3@att.com>\n",
